                        <item xml:id="e1">- The Pss. are divided into groups of ten separated by a line of alternating black and red dots. &#xD;
- The midpoint of the “Psalms of David” (in P<locus target="77">77</locus>) is marked on <locus target="48v">48v</locus> with an inscription in Amharic ኩሌታ (?): የዳዊት፡ አ.&#xD;
- Part of the line is taken up: e.g., <locus target="3v">3v</locus>, 5v, 15v, 30r, 40r, 56v, 83r, 105v.&#xD;
- Part of the line is taken down: <locus target="20v">20v</locus>, 92v, 121r. &#xD;
- Unreadable and mostly erased notes: <locus target="2v">2v</locus>, 3v.&#xD;
- Pen trials or writing exercises (from unidentified prayers to Mary): <locus target="103v">103v</locus>.</item>
